Problem: Minimum Common Value
Topic: Arrays, Two Pointers
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
Use two pointers to traverse both sorted arrays simultaneously. If the elements are equal, return the common value. Otherwise, move the pointer pointing to the smaller element. If no common element is found after traversing both arrays, return -1.

Time Complexity: O(n + m)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:

class Solution {
public:
    int getCommon(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        int n1 = nums1.size();
        int n2 = nums2.size();

        while (i < n1 && j < n2) {
            if (nums1[i] == nums2[j]) {
                return nums1[i]; 
            } else if (nums1[i] < nums2[j]) {
                i++; 
            } else {
                j++; 
            }
        }

        return -1;
    }
};
